01:38:33.891 --> 01:38:37.039
Shri Sahasrara Swamini

01:38:37.239 --> 01:38:41.399
Moksha Pradayini Mataji

01:38:41.600 --> 01:38:48.772
Shri Nirmala Devi Namoh Namaha.

01:38:48.972 --> 01:38:53.163
Shri Mataji: [Aside to the person] May God
bless you. Now let them come here.

01:39:00.750 --> 01:39:06.145
Rub it hard. Here. Void.

01:39:06.361 --> 01:39:09.203
[Gospel of Matthew: 6,1-6.16-18]
Then Christ said unto his disciples:

01:39:09.404 --> 01:39:13.431
²Therefore, when thou doest thine alms,
do not sound a trumpet before thee,

01:39:13.632 --> 01:39:16.446
as the hypocrites do in the synagogues
and in the streets

01:39:16.647 --> 01:39:18.665
that they may have glory of men.

01:39:18.866 --> 01:39:22.077
Verily I say unto you, They have their
reward.

01:39:22.278 --> 01:39:27.293
³But when thou doest alms, let not thy left
hand know what thy right hand doeth

01:39:27.494 --> 01:39:31.861
⁴that thine alms may be in secret; and thy
Father which sees thee in secret,

01:39:32.062 --> 01:39:35.434
himself shall reward thee openly.

01:39:35.635 --> 01:39:39.410
⁵And when thou prayest, thou shalt not be
as the hypocrites are,

01:39:39.611 --> 01:39:41.551
for they love to pray standing
in the synagogues

01:39:41.752 --> 01:39:45.414
and in the corners of the streets that they
may be seen of men.

01:39:45.615 --> 01:39:48.487
Verily I say unto you, They have their
reward.

01:39:48.688 --> 01:39:52.413
⁶But thou, when thou prayest, enter
into thy closet,

01:39:52.614 --> 01:39:56.458
and when thou hast shut thy door, pray
to thy Father which is in secret;

01:39:56.659 --> 01:40:00.636
and thy Father which sees thee in secret
shall reward thee openly.

01:40:00.837 --> 01:40:04.911
⁷But when ye pray, use not vain repetitions
as the heathen do,

01:40:05.112 --> 01:40:08.445
for they think that they shall be heard
for their much speaking.

01:40:08.646 --> 01:40:11.997
⁸Be not ye therefore like unto them,
for your Father knows

01:40:12.198 --> 01:40:15.357
what things ye have need of before
ye ask him.

01:40:15.558 --> 01:40:18.844
⁹After this manner pray therefore:

01:40:19.045 --> 01:40:23.712
Our Father who are in heavens,
Hallowed be thy name.

01:40:23.913 --> 01:40:25.812
¹⁰Thy kingdom come.

01:40:26.058 --> 01:40:30.456
Thy will be done in earth, as it is
in heaven.

01:40:30.657 --> 01:40:36.228
¹¹Give us this day our daily bread and
forgive us our trespasses,

01:40:36.445 --> 01:40:40.111
as we forgive those who trespass
against us;

01:40:40.312 --> 01:40:45.588
¹³And lead us not into temptation,
but deliver us from evil,

01:40:45.789 --> 01:40:49.967
for thine is the kingdom, the power
and the glory,

01:40:50.167 --> 01:40:54.900
forever and ever. Amen.

01:41:04.574 --> 01:41:06.652
Yogi: From the Gospel of Saint John.

01:41:06.852 --> 01:41:10.098
Shri Mataji: Good. Water… you take out
in… this water.

01:41:11.503 --> 01:41:13.666
¹Now before the feast of the passover,

01:41:13.867 --> 01:41:15.763
when Jesus knew that his hour was come

01:41:15.964 --> 01:41:18.854
that he should depart out of this world
unto the Father,

01:41:19.055 --> 01:41:23.333
having loved his own which were in the
world, he loved them unto the end.

01:41:23.534 --> 01:41:25.654
²And supper being ended,

01:41:25.855 --> 01:41:28.468
the devil having now put into the heart
of Judas Iscariot,

01:41:28.669 --> 01:41:30.866
Simon’s son, to betray him;

01:41:31.067 --> 01:41:34.647
³Jesus knowing that the Father had given
all things into his hands,

01:41:34.848 --> 01:41:38.335
and that he was come from God, and went
to God;

01:41:38.536 --> 01:41:41.485
⁴He riseth from supper, and laid aside
his garments;

01:41:41.686 --> 01:41:44.528
and took a towel, and girded himself.

01:41:44.729 --> 01:41:47.488
⁵After that he poureth water into a bason,

01:41:47.689 --> 01:41:50.291
and began to wash the disciples’ feet,

01:41:50.492 --> 01:41:54.527
and to wipe them with the towel wherewith
he was girded.

01:41:54.728 --> 01:41:58.372
⁶Then cometh he to Simon Peter: and Peter
saith unto him,

01:41:58.573 --> 01:42:01.684
Lord, dost thou wash my feet?

01:42:01.885 --> 01:42:04.004
⁷Jesus answered and said unto him,

01:42:04.205 --> 01:42:09.101
What I do thou knowest not now; but thou
shalt know hereafter.

01:42:09.302 --> 01:42:12.724
⁸Peter saith unto him, Thou shalt never
wash my feet.

01:42:12.925 --> 01:42:17.593
Jesus answered him, If I wash thee not,
thou hast no part with me.

01:42:17.802 --> 01:42:20.924
⁹Simon Peter saith unto him, Lord,
not my feet only,

01:42:21.124 --> 01:42:24.029
but also my hands and my head.

01:42:24.230 --> 01:42:28.192
¹⁰Jesus saith unto him, He that is washed

01:42:28.393 --> 01:42:32.433
needeth not save to wash his feet, but
is clean every whit:

01:42:32.634 --> 01:42:35.509
and ye are clean, but not all.

01:42:35.710 --> 01:42:38.870
¹¹For he knew who should betray him;
therefore said he,

01:42:39.071 --> 01:42:41.392
Ye are not all clean.

01:42:41.593 --> 01:42:44.384
¹²So after he had washed their feet, and
had taken his garments,

01:42:44.585 --> 01:42:47.292
and was set down again, he said unto them,

01:42:47.493 --> 01:42:49.517
Know ye what I have done to you?

01:42:49.718 --> 01:42:54.218
¹³Ye call me Master and Lord: and ye say
well; for so I am.

01:42:54.419 --> 01:42:57.208
¹⁴If I then, your Lord and Master, have
washed your feet;

01:42:57.409 --> 01:42:59.980
ye also ought to wash one another’s feet.

01:43:00.181 --> 01:43:03.889
¹⁵For I have given you an example, that
ye should do as I have done to you.

01:43:04.090 --> 01:43:06.352
¹⁶Verily, verily, I say unto you,

01:43:06.553 --> 01:43:09.013
The servant is not greater than his lord;

01:43:09.214 --> 01:43:12.557
neither he that is sent greater than he
that sent him.

01:43:12.758 --> 01:43:18.195
¹⁷If ye know these things, happy are ye
if ye do them.

01:43:31.617 --> 01:43:33.581
Other yogi [continues]: ¹⁸I speak not
of you all:

01:43:33.782 --> 01:43:36.484
I know whom I have chosen:

01:43:36.685 --> 01:43:39.361
but that the scripture may be fulfilled,

01:43:39.562 --> 01:43:44.468
He that eateth bread with me hath lifted up
his heel against me.

01:43:44.674 --> 01:43:46.769
¹⁹Now I tell you before it come,

01:43:46.969 --> 01:43:51.868
that, when it is come to pass, ye may
believe that I am he.

01:43:52.069 --> 01:43:55.006
²⁰Verily, verily, I say unto you…
Shri Mataji: Loudly.

01:43:55.207 --> 01:43:58.789
Yogi: He that receiveth whomsoever I send
receiveth me;

01:43:58.990 --> 01:44:03.571
and he that receiveth me receiveth him
that sent me.

01:44:03.772 --> 01:44:07.218
²¹When Jesus had thus said, he was troubled
in spirit,

01:44:07.419 --> 01:44:10.930
and testified, and said, Verily, verily,

01:44:11.131 --> 01:44:15.365
I say unto you, that one of you shall
betray me.

01:44:15.566 --> 01:44:21.322
²²Then the disciples looked upon one
another, doubting of whom he spake.

01:44:21.523 --> 01:44:27.476
²³Now there was leaning on Jesus’ bosom
one of his disciples, whom Jesus loved.

01:44:27.677 --> 01:44:29.949
²⁴Simon Peter therefore beckoned to him,

01:44:30.150 --> 01:44:34.253
that he should ask who it should be
of whom he spake.

01:44:34.454 --> 01:44:40.414
²⁵He then lying on Jesus’ breast saith
unto him, Lord, who is it?

01:44:40.615 --> 01:44:44.579
²⁶Jesus answered, He it is, to whom…

01:44:44.780 --> 01:44:46.008
Shri Mataji: Now somebody else should
read, because he has to wash…

01:44:46.208 --> 01:44:48.326
Yogi: I shall give a sop, when I have
dipped it.

01:44:48.527 --> 01:44:51.632
And when he had dipped the sop, he gave
it to Judas Iscariot,

01:44:51.833 --> 01:44:54.696
the son of Simon.

01:44:54.897 --> 01:44:57.152
Shri Mataji: Simon, you come.

01:44:57.353 --> 01:45:01.497
You come, both of you, then David will
do it also.

01:45:01.697 --> 01:45:06.527
He has to wash. Who else is there? David
and who else?

01:45:07.123 --> 01:45:11.812
Let Pat come to join David. Pat is there?
Come along.

01:45:12.012 --> 01:45:15.765
Yes. You wash my feet.

01:45:21.181 --> 01:45:23.863
Rub it hard.

01:45:27.371 --> 01:45:30.320
Other yogi: ²⁷And after the sop Satan
entered into him.

01:45:30.530 --> 01:45:35.636
Then Jesus said unto him, That thou
doest, do quickly.

01:45:35.837 --> 01:45:37.851
²⁸Now no man at the table knew

01:45:38.052 --> 01:45:40.981
for what intent he spake this unto him.

01:45:41.182 --> 01:45:44.528
²⁹For some of them thought, because Judas
had the bag,

01:45:44.729 --> 01:45:48.413
that Jesus had said unto him, Buy those
things

01:45:48.614 --> 01:45:51.432
that we have need of against the feast;

01:45:51.633 --> 01:45:54.737
or, that he should give something
to the poor.

01:45:54.938 --> 01:45:59.733
³⁰He then having received the sop went
immediately out: and it was night.

01:45:59.934 --> 01:46:03.044
³¹Therefore, when he was gone out,
Jesus said,

01:46:03.287 --> 01:46:07.949
Now is the Son of man glorified, and God
is glorified in him.

01:46:08.150 --> 01:46:10.496
³²And if God be glorified in him,

01:46:10.697 --> 01:46:16.829
God shall also glorify him in himself,

01:46:17.030 --> 01:46:19.572
and shall straightway glorify him.

01:46:19.773 --> 01:46:24.007
³³Little children, yet a little while I am
with you.

01:46:24.208 --> 01:46:29.218
Ye shall seek me: and as I said unto
the Jews,

01:46:29.419 --> 01:46:34.587
Whither I go, ye cannot come; so now
I say to you.

01:46:34.788 --> 01:46:37.060
³⁴A new commandment I give unto you,

01:46:37.261 --> 01:46:40.722
That ye shall love one another; as I have
loved you,

01:46:40.923 --> 01:46:44.212
that ye shall also love one another.

01:46:44.413 --> 01:46:48.628
³⁵By this shall all men know that ye are
my disciples,

01:46:48.829 --> 01:46:52.623
if ye have love one to another.

01:46:52.824 --> 01:46:59.066
³⁶Simon Peter said unto him, Lord, whither
goest thou?

01:46:59.267 --> 01:47:03.200
Jesus answered him, [Whither] I go,

01:47:03.438 --> 01:47:08.661
thou canst not follow me now; but thou
shalt follow me afterwards.

01:47:08.862 --> 01:47:13.559
³⁷Peter said unto him, Lord, why cannot
I follow thee now?

01:47:13.760 --> 01:47:16.282
I will lay down my life for thy sake.

01:47:16.485 --> 01:47:21.408
³⁸Jesus answered him, Wilt thou lay down
thy life for my sake?

01:47:21.609 --> 01:47:24.435
Verily, verily, I say unto thee,

01:47:24.636 --> 01:47:31.948
The cock shall not crow, till thou hast
denied me thrice.

01:47:41.576 --> 01:47:43.363
Shri Mataji: It’s all right. Put it
a little bit…

01:47:43.563 --> 01:47:45.677
Other yogi: ¹Let not your heart be
troubled:

01:47:45.878 --> 01:47:50.285
ye believe in God, believe also in me.

01:47:50.512 --> 01:47:54.752
²In my Father’s house are many mansions:

01:47:54.953 --> 01:47:58.399
if it were not so, I would have told you.

01:47:58.600 --> 01:48:00.877
I go to prepare a place for you.

01:48:01.078 --> 01:48:04.015
³And if I go and prepare a place for you,

01:48:04.250 --> 01:48:08.442
I will come again, and receive you unto
myself;

01:48:08.643 --> 01:48:13.392
that where I am, there ye may be also.

01:48:13.609 --> 01:48:18.803
⁴And whither I go ye know, and the way
ye know.

01:48:19.581 --> 01:48:25.150
⁵Thomas saith unto him, Lord, we know not
whither thou goest;

01:48:25.351 --> 01:48:28.586
and how can we know the way?

01:48:28.837 --> 01:48:35.527
⁶Jesus saith unto him, I am the way,
the truth, and the life:

01:48:35.728 --> 01:48:40.081
no man cometh unto the Father, but by me.

01:48:40.282 --> 01:48:45.206
⁷If ye had known me, ye should have known
my Father also:

01:48:45.407 --> 01:48:50.650
and from henceforth ye know him, and have
seen him.

01:48:51.278 --> 01:48:57.413
Shri Mataji: “Have seen Him”: see, this
point they miss!

01:49:01.576 --> 01:49:07.422
Yogi: ⁸Philip saith unto him, Lord, show us
the Father, and it sufficeth us.

01:49:07.623 --> 01:49:11.275
⁹Jesus saith unto him, Have I been so long
with you,

01:49:11.476 --> 01:49:15.398
and yet hast thou not known me, Philip?

01:49:15.599 --> 01:49:18.824
He that hath seen me hath seen the Father;

01:49:19.025 --> 01:49:22.883
and how sayest thou, Show us the Father?

01:49:23.092 --> 01:49:29.279
¹⁰Believest thou not that I am in
the Father, and the Father in me?

01:49:29.480 --> 01:49:33.490
The words that I speak unto you I speak
not of myself:

01:49:33.691 --> 01:49:38.527
but the Father that dwelleth in me,
he doeth the works.

01:49:38.728 --> 01:49:44.084
¹¹Believe me that I am in the Father,
and the Father in me:

01:49:44.285 --> 01:49:49.239
or else believe me for the very
works’ sake.

01:49:49.791 --> 01:49:55.634
¹²Verily, verily, I say unto you, He that
believeth on me,

01:49:55.835 --> 01:50:00.606
the works that I do shall he also do;

01:50:00.807 --> 01:50:06.277
and greater works than these shall he do;
because I go unto my Father.

01:50:06.480 --> 01:50:10.459
¹³And whatsoever ye shall ask in my name,
that will I do,

01:50:10.660 --> 01:50:14.376
that the Father may be glorified
in the Son.

01:50:14.577 --> 01:50:21.432
¹⁴If ye shall ask any thing in my name,
I will do it.

01:50:24.756 --> 01:50:28.247
Shri Mataji: Good, beautiful. Come.
Good, now:

01:50:28.448 --> 01:50:33.730
you can take this water in something
else this side. Take it.

01:50:38.558 --> 01:50:43.290
Take the other one now, better…

01:50:46.583 --> 01:50:50.801
Good. Yogi: ¹⁵If ye love me, keep my
commandments.

01:50:51.002 --> 01:50:56.083
Shri Mataji: Loudly. Yogi: ¹⁵If ye love me,
keep my commandments.

01:50:56.298 --> 01:51:01.475
¹⁶And I will pray the Father, and he shall
give you another Comforter,

01:51:01.718 --> 01:51:05.393
that he may abide with you for ever;

01:51:05.594 --> 01:51:09.627
¹⁷Even the Spirit of truth; whom the world
cannot receive,

01:51:09.828 --> 01:51:13.369
because it seeth him not, neither knoweth
him:

01:51:13.570 --> 01:51:20.381
but ye know him; for he dwelleth with you,
and shall be in you.

01:51:20.582 --> 01:51:25.415
¹⁸I will not leave you comfortless: I will
come to you.

01:51:25.615 --> 01:51:29.912
¹⁹Yet a little while, and the world seeth
me no more;

01:51:30.113 --> 01:51:36.370
but ye see me: because I live, ye shall
live also.

01:51:36.570 --> 01:51:41.044
²⁰At that day ye shall know that I am
in my Father,

01:51:41.244 --> 01:51:45.188
and ye in me, and I in you.

01:51:45.389 --> 01:51:49.097
²¹He that hath my commandments, and
keepeth them,

01:51:49.298 --> 01:51:53.858
he it is that loveth me: and he that
loveth me

01:51:54.059 --> 01:51:56.984
shall be loved of my Father and I will
love him …

01:51:57.185 --> 01:52:00.738
Shri Mataji: See now: First Commandment
he said, that you love each other.

01:52:00.939 --> 01:52:04.239
The disciples must love each other, he
didn’t say any Dick, Tom and Harry.

01:52:04.440 --> 01:52:07.503
First love the disciples, all of you should
love each other,

01:52:07.704 --> 01:52:10.436
that’s the main thing is. First thing
is that.

01:52:10.637 --> 01:52:16.735
Second is, “My father”. See
the relationship.

01:52:17.871 --> 01:52:23.037
Yogi: … and I will love him, and will
manifest myself to him.

01:52:23.238 --> 01:52:27.697
²²Judas saith unto him, not Iscariot, Lord,

01:52:27.898 --> 01:52:33.759
how is it that thou wilt manifest thyself
unto us, and not unto the world?

01:52:33.960 --> 01:52:37.657
²³Jesus answered and said unto him,

01:52:37.858 --> 01:52:40.851
If a man love me, he will keep my words:

01:52:41.052 --> 01:52:44.928
and my Father will love him, and we will
come unto him,

01:52:45.128 --> 01:52:48.048
and make our abode with him.

01:52:48.249 --> 01:52:53.140
²⁴He that loveth me not keepeth not
my sayings:

01:52:53.341 --> 01:52:58.512
and the word which ye hear is (not) mine,
but the Father’s which sent me.

01:52:58.713 --> 01:53:03.893
²⁵These things have I spoken unto you,
being yet present with you.

01:53:04.171 --> 01:53:07.651
²⁶But the Comforter, which is the Holy
Ghost,

01:53:07.852 --> 01:53:10.987
whom the Father will send in my name,

01:53:11.188 --> 01:53:15.761
he shall teach you all things, and bring
all things to your remembrance,

01:53:15.962 --> 01:53:19.456
whatsoever I have said unto you.

01:53:19.657 --> 01:53:24.650
²⁷Peace I leave with you, my peace I give
unto you:

01:53:24.861 --> 01:53:28.529
not as the world giveth, give I unto you.

01:53:28.730 --> 01:53:33.661
Let not your heart be troubled, neither
let it be afraid.

01:53:33.862 --> 01:53:36.981
²⁸Ye have heard how I said unto you,
I go away,

01:53:37.182 --> 01:53:41.980
and come again unto you. If ye loved me,

01:53:42.181 --> 01:53:45.802
ye would rejoice, because I said, I go
unto the Father:

01:53:46.003 --> 01:53:49.593
for my Father is greater than I.

01:53:56.798 --> 01:54:00.010
Shri Mataji: Good. Start it with the high
tones, will keep it up, you see.

01:54:00.210 --> 01:54:02.297
The thing is people must hear you.

01:54:02.497 --> 01:54:06.021
Good. Now just see the hands - vibrations.

01:54:06.222 --> 01:54:10.105
Gavin: And now I have told you before
it come to pass,

01:54:10.322 --> 01:54:14.936
that, when it is come to pass, ye might
believe.

01:54:15.137 --> 01:54:17.527
³⁰Hereafter I will not talk much with you:

01:54:17.728 --> 01:54:23.182
for the prince of this world cometh, and
hath nothing in me.

01:54:23.383 --> 01:54:26.719
³¹But that the world may know that I love
the Father;

01:54:26.920 --> 01:54:31.743
and as the Father gave me commandment,
even so I do.

01:54:31.944 --> 01:54:37.279
Shri Mataji: Hm!
Yogi: Arise, let us go hence.

01:54:39.345 --> 01:54:45.419
¹I am the true vine, and my Father is
the husbandman.

01:54:45.620 --> 01:54:51.357
²Every branch in me that beareth not fruit
he taketh away:

01:54:51.558 --> 01:54:55.219
and every branch that beareth fruit,
he purgeth it…

01:54:55.420 --> 01:54:59.914
Shri Mataji: See!
Gavin: …that it may bring forth more fruit.

01:55:00.939 --> 01:55:05.745
³Now ye are clean through the word which
I have spoken unto you.

01:55:05.946 --> 01:55:11.038
⁴Abide in me, and I in you.

01:55:11.239 --> 01:55:16.503
As the branch cannot bear fruit of itself,
except it abide in the vine;

01:55:16.704 --> 01:55:21.603
no more can ye, except ye abide in me.

01:55:21.819 --> 01:55:25.629
⁵I am the vine, ye are the branches:

01:55:25.830 --> 01:55:28.919
He that abideth in me, and I in him,

01:55:29.120 --> 01:55:32.545
the same bringeth forth much fruit:

01:55:32.746 --> 01:55:36.928
for without me ye can do nothing.

01:55:37.691 --> 01:55:43.099
⁶If a man abide not in me, he is cast forth
as a branch, and is withered;

01:55:43.300 --> 01:55:49.201
and men gather them, and cast them into
the fire, and they are burned.

01:55:49.844 --> 01:55:53.587
⁷If ye abide in me, and my words abide
in you,

01:55:53.788 --> 01:55:58.612
ye shall ask what ye will, and it shall be
done unto you.

01:55:58.813 --> 01:56:03.534
⁸Herein is my Father glorified, that ye
bear much fruit;

01:56:03.735 --> 01:56:07.643
so shall ye be my disciples.

01:56:08.882 --> 01:56:13.586
⁹As the Father hath loved me, so have I
loved you:

01:56:13.787 --> 01:56:17.198
continue ye in my love.

01:56:17.415 --> 01:56:21.777
¹⁰If ye keep my commandments, ye shall
abide in my love;

01:56:21.994 --> 01:56:28.593
even as I have kept my Father’s
commandments, and abide in his love.

01:56:30.833 --> 01:56:32.558
¹¹These things have I spoken unto you,
Shri Mataji: All right. Now come along.

01:56:32.759 --> 01:56:36.323
Gavin: ... that my joy might remain in you,
Shri Mataji: Now come.

01:56:36.524 --> 01:56:42.025
John and Don. Yes. Just take it ...

01:56:42.226 --> 01:56:46.923
Gavin:  and that your joy might be full.
Shri Mataji: ... in the bowl.

01:56:47.464 --> 01:56:54.227
¹²This is my commandment, That ye love
one another, as I have loved you.

01:56:57.659 --> 01:57:00.619
¹³Greater love hath no man than this,

01:57:00.820 --> 01:57:05.522
that a man lay down his life for his
friends.

01:57:05.723 --> 01:57:11.644
¹⁴Ye are my friends, if ye do whatsoever
I command you.

01:57:12.804 --> 01:57:15.669
¹⁵Henceforth I call you not servants;

01:57:15.870 --> 01:57:19.674
for the servant knoweth not what his lord
doeth:

01:57:19.890 --> 01:57:22.220
but I have called you friends;

01:57:22.421 --> 01:57:28.796
for all things that I have heard of my
Father I have made known unto you.

01:57:41.769 --> 01:57:48.882
Shri Mataji: Rub it hard. Hard. Hm.
Very hard.

01:57:49.083 --> 01:57:52.440
Yogi: ¹⁶Ye have not chosen me, but I have
chosen you,

01:57:52.641 --> 01:57:56.897
and ordained you, that ye should go forth
and bring forth fruit,

01:57:57.098 --> 01:58:01.286
and that your fruit should remain: that
whatsoever ye shall ask

01:58:01.487 --> 01:58:05.629
of the Father in my name, he may give
it to you.

01:58:05.830 --> 01:58:09.848
¹⁷These things I command you, that ye love
one another.

01:58:10.049 --> 01:58:14.360
¹⁸If the world hate you, ye know that it
hated me before it hated you.

01:58:14.561 --> 01:58:17.633
Shri Mataji: Throughout one Commandment.
Just see. Because He knew

01:58:17.834 --> 01:58:22.487
that if you don’t love each other, nobody
is going to believe you.

01:58:23.226 --> 01:58:28.595
Yogi: ¹⁹If ye were of the world, the world
would love his own:

01:58:28.806 --> 01:58:33.428
but because ye are not of the world, but
I have chosen you out of the world,

01:58:33.636 --> 01:58:36.916
therefore the world hateth you.

01:58:37.117 --> 01:58:39.832
²⁰Remember the word that I said unto you,

01:58:40.033 --> 01:58:43.273
The servant is not greater than his lord.

01:58:43.474 --> 01:58:48.205
If they have persecuted me, they will also
persecute you;

01:58:48.407 --> 01:58:53.569
if they have kept my saying, they will
keep yours also.

01:58:53.770 --> 01:58:58.524
²¹But all these things will they do unto
you for my name’s sake,

01:58:58.744 --> 01:59:02.095
because they know not him that sent me.

01:59:02.296 --> 01:59:08.932
²²If I had not come and spoken unto them,
they had not had sin…

01:59:09.133 --> 01:59:13.201
Shri Mataji: They had…?
Yogi [repeats]: They had not had sin.

01:59:13.402 --> 01:59:17.881
But now they have no cloak for their sin.

01:59:18.406 --> 01:59:22.379
²³He that hateth me hateth my Father also.

01:59:22.580 --> 01:59:27.089
²⁴If I had not done among them the works
which none other man did,

01:59:27.314 --> 01:59:34.795
they had not had sin: but now have they
both

01:59:35.025 --> 01:59:39.160
seen and hated both me and my Father.

01:59:39.361 --> 01:59:41.286
But this cometh to pass,

01:59:41.487 --> 01:59:45.094
that the word might be fulfilled that
is written in their law,

01:59:45.319 --> 01:59:53.217
They hated me without a cause.
Shri Mataji: See. Very true.

01:59:53.649 --> 01:59:58.499
Yogi: ²⁶But when the Comforter is come,
whom I will send unto you from the Father,

01:59:58.700 --> 02:00:02.733
even the Spirit of truth, which proceedeth
from the Father,

02:00:02.933 --> 02:00:07.440
he shall testify of me:
Shri Mataji: Spirit of Truth is the point.

02:00:07.649 --> 02:00:13.203
You see, you get the Spirit of Truth and
then testify, you can testify.

02:00:13.404 --> 02:00:15.984
Yogi: ²⁷And ye also shall bear witness,

02:00:16.185 --> 02:00:19.666
because ye have been with me from
the beginning.

02:00:19.867 --> 02:00:22.863
Shri Mataji: From the very beginning.

02:00:25.523 --> 02:00:28.601
Though in Hebrew it may not be he or she,
I think so.

02:00:28.802 --> 02:00:34.440
Not sure, but you see, must be some sort
of a gender person.

02:00:41.329 --> 02:00:45.061
Now stop your movement, just stop it.

02:00:45.269 --> 02:00:52.947
Just keep it steady. Absolutely. Steady it.

02:00:53.190 --> 02:00:55.836
Yogi: ¹These things have I spoken unto you,
Shri Mataji: You still you are moving.

02:00:56.036 --> 02:00:58.193
Yogi: that ye should not be offended.

02:00:58.394 --> 02:01:02.204
²They shall put you out of the synagogues:
yea, the time cometh,

02:01:02.405 --> 02:01:05.444
that whosoever killeth you will think that
he doeth God service.

02:01:05.645 --> 02:01:08.232
[Shri Mataji: “Better. Put your hands
towards me.”] Yogi: ³And these things will

02:01:08.433 --> 02:01:12.329
they do unto you, because they have not
known the Father, nor me.

02:01:12.530 --> 02:01:16.543
⁴But these things have I told you, that
when the time shall come,

02:01:16.744 --> 02:01:19.277
ye may remember that I told you of them.
[Shri Mataji: “All right?”]

02:01:19.478 --> 02:01:24.599
And these things I said not unto you at
the beginning, because I was with you.

02:01:24.800 --> 02:01:28.643
⁵But now I go my way to him that sent me;

02:01:28.844 --> 02:01:32.298
and none of you asketh me, Whither
goest thou?

02:01:32.499 --> 02:01:37.366
⁶But because I have said these things unto
you, sorrow hath filled your heart.

02:01:37.567 --> 02:01:43.061
⁷Nevertheless I tell you the truth; It is
expedient for you that I go away:

02:01:43.269 --> 02:01:46.655
for if I go not away, the Comforter will
not come unto you;

02:01:46.856 --> 02:01:50.032
but if I depart, I will send him unto you.

02:01:50.233 --> 02:01:53.150
⁸And when he is come, he will reprove
the world of sin,

02:01:53.351 --> 02:01:55.861
and of righteousness and of judgment.

02:01:56.062 --> 02:01:59.539
⁹Of sin, because they believe not on me;
¹⁰Of righteousness…

02:01:59.740 --> 02:02:03.769
Shri Mataji: I think you stand up, and say,
you see, because people can’t hear you.

02:02:03.970 --> 02:02:06.875
See now how clearly, again, just read it.

02:02:07.076 --> 02:02:09.291
How clear it is. What a nice chapter today.

02:02:09.492 --> 02:02:14.223
Yogi: ⁷Nevertheless I tell you the truth;
It is expedient for you that I go away:

02:02:14.424 --> 02:02:17.841
for if I go not away, the Comforter will
not come unto you;

02:02:18.042 --> 02:02:21.420
but if I depart, I will send Her unto you.

02:02:21.621 --> 02:02:24.710
⁸And when She is come, She will reprove
the world of sin,

02:02:24.911 --> 02:02:27.869
and of righteousness and of judgment:

02:02:28.070 --> 02:02:30.422
⁹Of sin, because they believe not on me;

02:02:30.623 --> 02:02:34.862
¹⁰Of righteousness, because I go to my
Father, and ye see me no more;

02:02:35.063 --> 02:02:38.946
¹¹Of judgment, because the prince of this
world is judged.

02:02:39.147 --> 02:02:43.523
¹²I have yet many things to say unto you,
but ye cannot hear (bear) them now.

02:02:43.724 --> 02:02:46.194
Howbeit when She, the Spirit of truth,
is come,

02:02:46.395 --> 02:02:51.754
She will guide you into all truth: for She
shall not speak (of) himself;

02:02:51.955 --> 02:02:56.981
but whatsoever She shall hear, that shall
She speak:

02:02:57.182 --> 02:03:01.740
and She will shew you things to come.
Shri Mataji: Whatsoever She saw.

02:03:01.948 --> 02:03:03.725
Yogi (repeats): … and SHE will shew you
things to come.

02:03:03.926 --> 02:03:08.469
Shri Mataji: No, before this sentence,
what is it?

02:03:09.986 --> 02:03:13.124
Yogi (repeats): ¹³Howbeit when Her,
the Spirit of truth, is come,

02:03:13.359 --> 02:03:17.961
She will guide you into all truth: for She
shall not speak of Herself;

02:03:18.162 --> 02:03:25.808
but whatsoever She shall hear, that
shall She speak:

02:03:26.009 --> 02:03:28.513
and She will shew you things to come.

02:03:28.714 --> 02:03:31.867
¹⁴She shall glorify me: for She shall
receive of mine,

02:03:32.068 --> 02:03:34.347
and shall shew it unto you.

02:03:34.548 --> 02:03:38.410
¹⁵All things that the Father hath are mine:
therefore said I,

02:03:38.611 --> 02:03:42.805
that She shall take of mine, and shall
shew it unto you.

02:03:43.006 --> 02:03:46.198
¹⁶A little while, and ye shall not see me:
and again, a little while,

02:03:46.399 --> 02:03:50.064
and ye shall see me, because I go
to the Father.

02:03:54.039 --> 02:03:58.644
Shri Mataji: Now better? Yes, better.

02:04:03.135 --> 02:04:07.422
Better now? Just see on his head. Are
you alright?

02:04:08.440 --> 02:04:12.420
He is alright. Alright. Now.

02:04:13.261 --> 02:04:16.246
May God bless you.

02:04:18.144 --> 02:04:23.986
Other yogi: ¹⁷Then said some of his
disciples among themselves,

02:04:24.187 --> 02:04:27.577
What is this that he saith unto thee,

02:04:27.777 --> 02:04:31.372
What is this that he saith unto us,

02:04:31.573 --> 02:04:36.131
A little while, and ye shall not see me:

02:04:36.332 --> 02:04:42.662
and again, a little while, and ye shall
see me:

02:04:42.863 --> 02:04:47.170
(and), Because I go unto the Father?

02:04:47.371 --> 02:04:54.042
¹⁸They said therefore, What is this that
he saith, A little while?

02:04:54.243 --> 02:04:58.355
He cannot tell what he saith.

02:04:58.556 --> 02:05:06.594
¹⁹Now Jesus knew that they were desirous
to ask him, and said unto them,

02:05:06.797 --> 02:05:11.657
Do ye inquire among yourselves of that
I said,

02:05:11.858 --> 02:05:15.488
A little while, and ye shall not see me:

02:05:15.689 --> 02:05:22.357
and again, a little while, and ye shall
see me?

02:05:22.616 --> 02:05:30.117
²⁰Verily, verily, I say unto you, That ye
shall weep and lament,

02:05:30.318 --> 02:05:36.279
but the world shall rejoice: and ye shall
be sorrowful,

02:05:36.574 --> 02:05:42.554
but your sorrow shall be turned into joy.

02:05:42.755 --> 02:05:47.370
²¹A woman when she is in travail hath
sorrow,

02:05:47.571 --> 02:05:50.596
because her hour is come:

02:05:50.797 --> 02:05:55.235
but as soon as she is delivered
of the child,

02:05:55.436 --> 02:06:00.105
she remembereth no more the anguish,

02:06:00.306 --> 02:06:06.105
for joy that a man is born unto the world.

02:06:06.306 --> 02:06:13.069
²²And ye now therefore - and ye now
therefore have sorrow:

02:06:13.270 --> 02:06:20.830
but I will see, but I will see you again,
and your heart shall rejoice,

02:06:21.046 --> 02:06:25.194
and your joy no man taketh from you.

02:06:25.395 --> 02:06:29.931
²³And in that day ye shall ask me nothing.

02:06:30.132 --> 02:06:35.532
Shri Mataji: In that day, you see? You
shall ask me nothing.

02:06:39.453 --> 02:06:44.074
Yogi: Verily, verily, I say unto you,
Whatsoever ye shall ask

02:06:44.275 --> 02:06:49.731
the Father in my name, he shall give
it you.

02:06:49.932 --> 02:06:53.678
²⁴Hitherto have ye asked nothing in my
name:

02:06:53.879 --> 02:07:01.173
ask, and ye shall receive, that your joy
may be full.

02:07:01.374 --> 02:07:05.039
²⁵These things have I spoken unto you
in proverbs:

02:07:05.240 --> 02:07:11.112
but the time cometh, when I shall no more
speak unto you in proverbs,

02:07:11.313 --> 02:07:16.225
but I shall shew you plainly of the Father.

02:07:16.426 --> 02:07:19.849
²⁶At that time of day ye shall ask in my
name:

02:07:20.050 --> 02:07:27.370
and I say not unto you, that I will pray
the Father for you:

02:07:27.571 --> 02:07:32.806
²⁷For the Father himself loveth you,
because ye have loved me,

02:07:33.007 --> 02:07:37.780
and have believed that I came from God.

02:07:37.981 --> 02:07:43.810
Shri Mataji: Beautiful. Now what more
you want? Said everything!

02:07:47.700 --> 02:07:52.652
Read the Resurrection part, somewhere.

02:07:55.287 --> 02:08:01.064
All right. First here make…

02:08:02.104 --> 02:08:07.846
this side. Did you tell?

02:08:08.820 --> 02:08:11.408
Good. Here.

02:08:30.494 --> 02:08:33.884
Now put your hands towards me.

02:08:39.504 --> 02:08:44.251
All right? Good.

02:08:46.979 --> 02:08:56.150
Now. Can we – I was thinking – all right,

02:08:56.426 --> 02:09:00.678
for Mandy and Magda,

02:09:01.465 --> 02:09:05.317
you can come and wash my hands.

02:09:17.537 --> 02:09:20.843
Ken, one of the things.

02:09:25.963 --> 02:09:29.509
If you can bring a bucket or something
you can put on that…

02:09:29.725 --> 02:09:34.099
Yogi: [John, 19.41] ⁴¹Now in the place
where he was crucified there was a garden;

02:09:34.334 --> 02:09:40.327
and in the garden a new sepulchre, wherein
was never man yet laid.

02:09:40.528 --> 02:09:45.476
⁴²There laid they Jesus therefore because
of the Jews’ preparation day;

02:09:45.751 --> 02:09:49.983
or the sepulchre was nigh at hand.

02:09:50.184 --> 02:09:54.368
¹The first day of the week cometh Mary
Magdalene early,

02:09:54.569 --> 02:09:57.412
when it was yet dark, unto the sepulchre,

02:09:57.613 --> 02:10:01.131
seeth the stone taken away from
the sepulchre.

02:10:01.332 --> 02:10:05.157
[Shri Mataji: “Get a bucket or something”.]
Then she runneth, and cometh to Simon Peter,

02:10:05.358 --> 02:10:10.099
and to the other disciple, whom Jesus
loved, and saith unto them,

02:10:10.300 --> 02:10:13.055
They have taken away the Lord out
of the sepulchre,

02:10:13.256 --> 02:10:16.193
and we do not know where they have laid
him. [Shri Mataji: “Some bucket”.]

02:10:16.394 --> 02:10:21.747
³Peter therefore went forth, and that other
disciple, and came to the sepulchre.

02:10:21.948 --> 02:10:26.450
⁴So they ran both together: and the other
disciple did outrun Peter,

02:10:26.651 --> 02:10:29.303
and came first to the sepulchre.

02:10:29.504 --> 02:10:35.046
⁵And he stooping down, and looking in,
saw the linen clothes lying;

02:10:35.247 --> 02:10:37.135
yet went he not in.

02:10:37.336 --> 02:10:40.021
⁶Then cometh Simon Peter following him,

02:10:40.222 --> 02:10:44.811
and went into the sepulchre, and seeth
the linen clothes lie,

02:10:45.012 --> 02:10:49.642
⁷And the napkin, that was about his head,
not lying with the linen clothes,

02:10:49.843 --> 02:10:53.273
but wrapped together in a place by itself.

02:10:53.474 --> 02:10:55.632
⁸Then went in also that other disciple,

02:10:55.833 --> 02:11:00.039
which came first to the sepulchre, and he
saw, and believed.

02:11:00.242 --> 02:11:05.571
⁹For as yet they knew not the scripture,
that he must rise again from the dead.

02:11:05.772 --> 02:11:11.346
¹⁰Then the disciples went away again
unto their own home.

02:11:11.547 --> 02:11:14.985
¹¹But Mary stood without at the sepulchre
weeping:

02:11:15.186 --> 02:11:19.487
and as she wept, she stooped down, and
looked into the sepulchre,

02:11:19.688 --> 02:11:22.592
¹²And seeth two angels in white sitting,

02:11:22.793 --> 02:11:25.347
the one at the head, and the other
at the feet,

02:11:25.548 --> 02:11:28.287
where the body of Jesus had lain.

02:11:28.488 --> 02:11:33.093
¹³And they say unto her, Woman, why
weepest thou?

02:11:33.294 --> 02:11:37.367
She saith unto them, Because they have
taken away my Lord,

02:11:37.568 --> 02:11:40.672
and I know not where they have laid him.

02:11:40.873 --> 02:11:44.501
¹⁴And when she had thus said, she
turned herself back,

02:11:44.702 --> 02:11:50.277
and saw Jesus standing, and knew not
that it was Jesus.

02:11:50.478 --> 02:11:53.914
¹⁵Jesus saith unto her, Woman, why
weepest thou?

02:11:54.125 --> 02:11:56.554
Whom seekest thou?

02:11:56.755 --> 02:12:00.517
She, supposing him to be the gardener,
saith unto him,

02:12:00.721 --> 02:12:06.232
Sir, if thou have borne him hence, take
(tell) me where thou hast laid him,

02:12:06.432 --> 02:12:09.300
and I will take him away.

02:12:09.501 --> 02:12:12.766
¹⁶Jesus saith unto her, Mary.

02:12:12.967 --> 02:12:20.822
She turned herself, and saith unto him,
Rabboni; which is to say, Master.

02:12:21.023 --> 02:12:24.162
Jesus saith unto her, Touch me not;

02:12:24.363 --> 02:12:27.516
for I am not yet ascended to my Father:

02:12:27.717 --> 02:12:30.807
but go to my brethren, and say unto them,

02:12:31.008 --> 02:12:34.376
I ascend unto my Father, and your Father;

02:12:34.577 --> 02:12:39.056
and to my God, and your God.

02:12:48.357 --> 02:12:52.246
Shri Mataji: Left is catching. Just rub
this left foot.

02:12:52.446 --> 02:12:56.625
Rub it. Just rub the left. All right.

02:12:56.865 --> 02:13:04.585
See, these two, two fingers up here, see,
Vishuddhi and Agnya. Rub it hard.

02:13:13.797 --> 02:13:18.564
Other yogi: ¹⁸Mary Magdalene came and told
the disciples that she had seen the Lord,

02:13:18.765 --> 02:13:22.912
and that he had spoken these things
unto her.

02:13:23.113 --> 02:13:27.255
¹⁹Then the same day at evening, being
the first day of the week,

02:13:27.456 --> 02:13:30.449
when the doors were shut where
the disciples were assembled

02:13:30.650 --> 02:13:34.761
for fear of the Jews, came Jesus and stood
in the midst,

02:13:34.962 --> 02:13:39.155
and saith unto them, Peace be unto you.

02:13:39.356 --> 02:13:46.016
²⁰And when he had so said, he shewed
unto them his hands and his side.

02:13:46.217 --> 02:13:50.886
Then were the disciples glad, when they
saw the Lord.

02:13:51.087 --> 02:13:54.899
²¹Then said Jesus to them again,
Peace be unto you:

02:13:55.100 --> 02:14:00.182
as my Father hath sent me, even so
send I you.

02:14:00.383 --> 02:14:04.210
²²And when he had said this, he breathed
on them,

02:14:04.411 --> 02:14:09.780
and saith unto them, Receive ye the Holy
Ghost:

02:14:09.981 --> 02:14:15.475
²³Whose soever sins ye remit, they are
remitted unto them;

02:14:15.676 --> 02:14:20.941
and whose soever sins ye retain, they
are retained.

02:14:21.142 --> 02:14:25.629
²⁴But Thomas, one of the twelve, called
Didymus,

02:14:25.830 --> 02:14:29.189
was not with them when Jesus came.

02:14:29.390 --> 02:14:34.147
²⁵The other disciples therefore said unto
him, We have seen the Lord.

02:14:34.348 --> 02:14:40.280
But he said unto them, Except I shall see
in his hands the print of the nails,

02:14:40.481 --> 02:14:43.031
and put my finger into the print
of the nails,

02:14:43.232 --> 02:14:47.861
and thrust my hand into his side, I will
not believe.

02:14:48.062 --> 02:14:52.222
²⁶And after eight days again his disciples
were within,

02:14:52.423 --> 02:14:58.203
and Thomas with them: then came Jesus,
the doors being shut,

02:14:58.404 --> 02:15:02.572
and stood in the midst, and said, Peace
be unto you.

02:15:02.773 --> 02:15:09.132
²⁷Then saith he to Thomas, Reach hither
thy finger, and behold my hands;

02:15:09.333 --> 02:15:13.935
and reach hither thy hand, and thrust it
into my side:

02:15:14.136 --> 02:15:17.327
and be not faithless, but believing.

02:15:17.528 --> 02:15:23.431
²⁸And Thomas answered and said unto him,
My Lord and my God.

02:15:23.632 --> 02:15:30.494
²⁹Jesus saith unto him, Thomas, because
thou hast seen me, thou hast believed:

02:15:30.695 --> 02:15:35.298
blessed are they that have not seen,
and yet have believed.

02:15:35.499 --> 02:15:39.978
³⁰And many other signs truly did Jesus
in the presence of his disciples,

02:15:40.179 --> 02:15:43.993
which are not written in this book:
³¹But these are written,

02:15:44.194 --> 02:15:48.730
that ye might believe that Jesus is
the Christ, the Son of God;

